  "text": "[8] For these four models, we analyze the monthly sea ice concentration for both the \"preindustrial\" and \"historical\" scenarios [CITATION_1] . For the former, a 500-year long simulation is available for each model (except CESM1-WACCM, for which only 200 years were archived). For the latter, we focus on the period 1979-2005, when model output overlaps with observations: For that 27-year period, three-member ensembles are available for the CESM models but only one simulation each for the GFDL models. In all cases, we calculate SIE by summing the areas of all grid cells with sea ice concentration exceeding 15%, and we calculate trends as least squares linear fits to the SIE time series.",
